  "prompt": "The income paid/credited showing on my 26AS statement is Rs. 1,25,367.44 (salary income) and on Form 16, the total income shown is Rs 1,33,209 (after deducting PF). Which one should I show in ITR 1 under 'Income from Chargeable Salaries'?",
  "response": "When filing your Income Tax Return (ITR), you should use the total income after deductions as shown in Form 16 for reporting your \"Income from Chargeable Salaries.\" Form 16 is the certificate issued by your employer that summarizes your salary income and the deductions made. \n\nYour Form 26AS shows the details of the income credited to your account and the TDS deducted by the employer but does not necessarily reflect any deductions like PF, standard deduction, tax-saving investments, etc. On the other hand, Form 16 provides a comprehensive summary after accounting for these deductions.\n\nIn your case, the amount of Rs. 1,33,209 shown on Form 16 (after deducting PF) should be reported under 'Income from Chargeable Salaries' in ITR 1. Ensure all necessary details match up and reconcile the figures provided in Form 16 and Form 26AS. \n\nDo keep both documents handy and cross-check the details for any discrepancies. If there is any issue or inconsistency, consulting with a tax advisor or the payroll department in your organization may help clarify and resolve the matter.",
